benchmark: butter_multires_strip_2026-05-22.csv
date: 2026-05-22
host: lilith
gpu: NVIDIA GeForce RTX 5070
driver: 596.21
cuda: 13.2
master_tip: 220b6250fe5d70996abd62410e96461033e97946
worktree_head: feat/butter-multires-strip (uncommitted at bench time)
command: cargo run --release -p butteraugli-gpu --features cuda,cubecl-types --example bench_multires_strip_vs_whole_cuda
backend: cubecl-cuda (CudaRuntime)
body_h: 256
halo_h: 40
sizes: 4MP_2000x2000, 12MP_4000x3000, 24MP_6144x4096
notes:
  - 24 MP whole-image is skipped (exceeds 12 GB GPU memory budget).
  - 4 MP strip is SLOWER than whole because per-strip kernel-launch
    overhead exceeds the locality win at this size. This matches the
    single-res strip behavior and is expected.
  - 12 MP strip is 11.3× faster than whole — whole spills past L2.
  - All numbers are zenbench medians over 4 rounds with one warmup
    call before timed runs.
